stories.text:
I really like Cloudflare and use it on all my sites because of their generous free plan. But I'm not sure how to feel about one company routing 20 % of internet traffic and counting.

Is there any competitor worth a look?

Edit: It's 20 % of all websites supposedly, not of all web traffic, but I think the point still stands

stories.text: I have a computer science / math education. I love creating software and I'm quite skilled at it. But, I'm also very interested in physics and astronomy, and I greatly admire the people who push those fields forward. I want to write tools for scientists in my free time, but I don't know what they need. How do I find out?
